issues.title: Carbon Fiber Body Panel Cracking
issues.description: Carbon fiber body panels, particularly around door frames and side panels, developing stress cracks or delamination issues, especially in areas subject to thermal cycling or minor impacts.
symptoms: Visible hairline cracks in carbon fiber
issues.fix_description: Complete replacement of affected carbon fiber panels with updated parts from Maserati
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature changes, careful parking to prevent minor impacts, regular inspection

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing and Boot Loops
issues.description: The central infotainment system experiences frequent freezing, black screens, or gets stuck in boot loops, requiring system resets or software updates.
issues.fix_description: Software update or complete infotainment unit replacement if hardware failure
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoid extreme temperatures, gentle handling of touchscreen

issues.title: Suspension System Premature Wear
issues.description: Adaptive suspension components, particularly shock absorbers and electronic dampers, showing premature wear or failure, leading to reduced ride quality and handling issues.
issues.fix_description: Replacement of worn suspension components with updated parts
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive driving over rough surfaces, regular suspension inspections

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: Butterfly door handle mechanisms failing to operate correctly, either becoming stuck in closed position or failing to properly latch when closing.
issues.fix_description: Replacement of door handle mechanism and associated actuators
issues.prevention: Gentle operation of door handles, regular lubrication of mechanism

issues.title: Engine Oil Temperature Management Issues
issues.description: V6 Nettuno engine experiencing oil temperature regulation problems, leading to overheating warnings or engine protection mode activation during track use or aggressive driving.
issues.fix_description: Oil cooler system upgrade or replacement, software calibration updates
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper grade oil, allow proper warm-up periods

issues.title: Brake System Premature Pad Wear
issues.description: Carbon ceramic brake pads wearing prematurely or unevenly, particularly during normal driving conditions, leading to reduced braking performance.
issues.fix_description: Replacement of brake pads and possible rotor resurfacing or replacement
issues.prevention: Proper brake bedding procedure, avoid aggressive braking when cold

issues.title: Electrical Charging System Faults
issues.description: Battery charging system experiencing intermittent faults, leading to battery drain or charging warnings, particularly affecting vehicles with extended storage periods.
issues.fix_description: Alternator replacement or charging system component repair
issues.prevention: Use battery tender during storage, regular driving to maintain charge

issues.title: Paint Quality and Adhesion Problems
issues.description: Paint finish showing premature wear, chipping, or adhesion issues, particularly on high-stress areas like door edges and front fascia.
issues.fix_description: Repainting of affected panels with improved paint process
issues.prevention: Regular washing and waxing, covered parking when possible

issues.title: Climate Control System Malfunctions
issues.description: HVAC system experiencing issues with temperature control, fan speed regulation, or complete system failure, particularly affecting cabin comfort.
issues.fix_description: Replacement of HVAC control modules or actuator motors
issues.prevention: Regular system maintenance, avoid extreme temperature settings

issues.title: Fuel System Vapor Lock Issues
issues.description: Fuel delivery system experiencing vapor lock conditions during hot weather or track use, leading to fuel starvation and engine performance issues.
issues.fix_description: Fuel system component replacement or cooling system enhancement
issues.prevention: Avoid running on low fuel, use high-quality fuel, limit extended idling

editorial.tagline: Trident returns to supercar royalty with twin-turbo fury
editorial.hero_blurb: The MC20 marks Maserati's triumphant return to the supercar arena after nearly two decades. With its revolutionary Nettuno V6 and carbon fiber monocoque, this mid-engine masterpiece delivers 621 horsepower of Italian passion wrapped in stunning design.
editorial.essence: The MC20 represents Maserati's renaissance, combining cutting-edge technology with pure emotional appeal. Its twin-turbo Nettuno engine showcases Formula 1-derived innovations, while the carbon monocoque chassis delivers supercar dynamics with surprising daily usability.
editorial.heritage: Born from Maserati's racing DNA and MC12 legacy, the MC20 revives the brand's supercar ambitions after the MC12's production ended in 2005. The name honors Maserati Corse 2020, marking a new chapter in the trident's motorsport heritage while paying homage to legends like the Birdcage and Tipo 61.
editorial.design_philosophy: Clean, purposeful lines define the MC20's aesthetic, with every curve serving aerodynamic function. The designers pursued timeless Italian elegance over flashy aggression, creating a silhouette that's both modern and unmistakably Maserati through subtle details like the signature grille and butterfly doors.
editorial.motorsport_history: While the MC20 is newly born, it carries forward Maserati's illustrious racing legacy from Formula 1 victories in the 1950s to the MC12's GT1 championship success. The car serves as a technological showcase for Maserati's return to competitive motorsport with the MC20 GT2 racer.
editorial.engine_character: The Nettuno V6 delivers explosive power with surprising refinement, featuring F1-derived pre-chamber ignition technology. It builds torque linearly from low RPMs before unleashing a crescendo of fury past 5,000 RPM, offering both tractable street manners and track-ready aggression.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 8-speed dual-clutch transmission shifts with precision and aggression in Corsa mode, while offering smooth, refined operation during casual driving. Paddle responses are immediate, and the transmission intelligently anticipates driver needs during spirited driving.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The carbon fiber monocoque provides exceptional rigidity while maintaining compliance over road imperfections. Adaptive dampers offer genuine versatility between comfort and track-focused settings, with predictable, confidence-inspiring behavior at the limit.
editorial.steering_feel: Precise and beautifully weighted, the steering communicates road surface details without being harsh. The electric system provides consistent feel across all driving modes, offering the perfect balance between assistance and connection to the front wheels.
editorial.brake_confidence: Brembo carbon-ceramic brakes deliver tremendous stopping power with excellent pedal feel and fade resistance. The system provides strong initial bite with progressive feel, inspiring confidence during aggressive track sessions while remaining manageable in daily driving.
editorial.sound_signature: The Nettuno produces a distinctive twin-turbo growl that's both sophisticated and aggressive, with satisfying pops and crackles on overrun. The active exhaust system transforms from civilized purr to race-car wail, creating an authentic Italian soundtrack without being obnoxious.
editorial.ideal_owner: Sophisticated enthusiasts who want cutting-edge Italian engineering with the practicality to use regularly, valuing exclusivity and technological innovation over pure brand prestige.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Badge collectors seeking maximum status, traditionalists preferring naturally aspirated engines, or those needing significant cargo space and easy entry/exit for passengers.
editorial.buyers_summary: The MC20 offers genuine supercar performance with impressive daily usability and exclusive appeal. While more expensive than some rivals, it delivers unique Italian character with cutting-edge technology that few manufacturers can match.

SETTING: Private collector's industrial warehouse garage. Brick warehouse with arched windows OR modern concrete gallery OR vintage factory with timber beams.

LIGHTING: Golden hour sunlight streaming through large industrial windows. Warm color temperature. Cinematic depth.

TECHNICAL: Magazine-quality automotive photography. Photorealistic, no CGI look. No people, no text, no watermarks, no logos, no license plates.
